3.5 Deep Mantle Reservoir Signatures
High-magnitude seismic events (M &gt; 4.0) occurred systematically at 30-40 km depths throughout the study period. These deeper events, while less frequent than shallow activity, demonstrate continuous activity within the proposed deep mantle reservoir system.

